  "title": "Interrogation Resistance Training, Day Two",
  "summary": "Continuing the ISB resistance-training ordeal, the ISB Agent Dreven Mercurio enters the cell of the Imperial pilot Liza Molokai, dehydrated and chained, to break her resolve. He shows her a live holofeed of her parents, a retired TIE pilot and his wife, forced to their knees at gunpoint, and counts down to their execution to coerce her submission; Liza refuses to break and the agents shoot her parents dead. Dreven then conducts a clinical session of torture, injecting her with a drug that turns her headache into a migraine, slicing incisions and inserting electrified probes into her body, and burning her from the inside until she finally cries out that she gives in. Coldly explaining that he himself is merely an instrument of the Emperor's will, Dreven informs her that she will instead break for a younger agent to earn him a commendation, threatening to remove her Sarian spots with acid if she refuses. He removes the probes, orders bacta applied, and departs, leaving the vial of acid just out of reach as Liza passes into a restless, haunted sleep.",
